         <abstract>
            <p>A cyclic sum $S(\mathbf{x}) = \Sigma x_i/(x_{i + 1} + x_{i + 2})$ is formed with the $N$ components of a vector $\mathbf{x}$, where $x_{N + 1} = x_1, x_{N + 2} = x_2$, and where all denominators are positive and all numerators are nonnegative. It is known that there exist vectors $\mathbf{x}$ for which $S(\mathbf{x}) &lt; N/2$ if $N \geq 14$ and even, and if $N \geq 25$. It has been proved that the inequality $S(\mathbf{x}) \geq N/2$ holds for $N \leq 12$. Although it has been conjectured repeatedly that the inequality also holds for odd $N$ between 13 and 23, this has apparently not yet been proved. Here we will confirm that the inequality indeed holds for $N = 13$.</p>
          </abstract>
